path.id: We let i range over all positions in A (from 0 to len(A) - 1) in each repetition of the loop, find the index imin that contains the smallest element in A[i], A[i+1], ... we then bring A[imin] in the i-th position by swapping A[i] and A[imin]
findMin(i, A) finds the smallest element in A[i], A[i+1], ... it goes through all of them and stores in imin the position of the smallest so far.
